Plosser Says Threat of Deflation Would Warrant More Fed Stimulus

-- B y   C a r o l i n e   S a l a s   G a g e
-- 
2011-10-12T19:04:52Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-12/plosser-says-threat-of-deflation-would-warrant-more-fed-stimulus.html
Federal Reserve Bank of Philadelphia
President  Charles Plosser  said today that the threat of
deflation would warrant more Fed stimulus. Plosser, speaking to
reporters after a speech in Philadelphia, said that more Fed
action would also be warranted in a crisis.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Caroline Salas Gage in New York at 
 csalas1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Kevin Costelloe at 
